1920s Hollywood BUT DESI! üíñ

Look 1: 
Saree & blouse- @labelankitajain 
Gold & gilded glamour. Prominent bead work on the saree, draped on a satin petticoat are all reminiscent of the 1920s. 

Look 2: 
Custom fringe kurta & dupatta- @puneetkapoorlabel 
Reminiscing the flapper girl era of the 1920s. Kurta dress right below the knee, baring the arms with finger waves for the hair. 

Look 3: 
Custom saree- @sunainakhera 
Faux fur coat- Zara 
Feather, fur boa and some champagne. This outfit is the perfect Bollywood twist to a Hollywood 1920s look. 

Look 4: 
Custom sharara suit- @puneetkapoorlabel 
Women loved drench themselves in sequins and beads from the 1920s. However, the dresses had modest necklines and were never fitted to the body. 

Look 5: 
Shirt- very old 
Saree- @arpitamehtaofficial
Button down shirts with tier skirts and brooches are again reminiscent of the 1920s. The tier saree is the perfect twist to the knee-length tier skirt.

Things I wish I knew earlier üíó

I realised lately that prioritising your own self is non-negotiable. We, as women, always go a little out of our way for the efforts we put and forget to do the same when it comes to caring for our health, be it mental or physical. 

Living out our lives to the fullest means being able to enjoy every moment in our life. And that can be done only when we actively take steps to ensure that we are in the pink of our health, every day.

One day isn‚Äôt enough to celebrate women and their journey towards self-love that needs no validation. So here is to enjoying the little things in life and making every day Women‚Äôs Day by prioritising our health. Join me and @maxhealthcare in celebrating #ItsOkayToBeImperfect and embracing our imperfections.
